{"module_name":"allocate-character-buffer-inside-memory-arena","package_name":"allocate-character-buffer-inside-memory-arena","build_type":"library","description":"Foundation L2 keystone: a glibc-free bump allocator. Reserves memory in 1 MiB chunks via the raw mmap syscall (no malloc), hands out 16-byte-aligned slices by advancing a module-global cursor, and never frees (the compiler is a short-lived process; the kernel reclaims the whole arena on exit). Variant-A-pure native schema: globals read/written via global_read/global_write into temps; the 16-byte align mask is written as the decimal -16 (atoi(\"~15\") would silently yield 0); the chunk-exhaustion test reads both globals into temps before the numeric compare; mmap syscall arguments are declared locals (the native syscall reads slots). Underpins the freestanding strdup, output buffers, and the document-value node store. A request larger than 1 MiB gets a dedicated chunk of exactly the padded request size (the chunk length and the recorded arena end both use the grown length), so oversized allocations are safe.","module_globals":[{"global_name":"arena_cursor_address","global_type":"i64","global_init":"0"},{"global_name":"arena_end_address","global_type":"i64","global_init":"0"},{"global_name":"arena_bytes_handed_out","global_type":"i64","global_init":"0"},{"global_name":"g_arena_budget","global_type":"i64","global_init":"0"},{"global_name":"g_arena_fixed","global_type":"i64","global_init":"0"}],"function_definitions":{"allocate-character-buffer-inside-memory-arena":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"size","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"size_padded","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"fifteen","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":15},{"instruction_type":"alu_operation","op